cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.CE 

This paper is about neuromorphic computing systems, which are designed to emulate the behavior of biological neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of hybrid analog/digital circuits, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.ET (Embedded Systems). The paper also discusses routing strategies and memory structures, which could place it in cs.EM (Emerging Technologies) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
